    "body": "Did you see this information at [Etherscan,.io](https://etherscan.io/chartsync/chaindefault)?\r\n I have also been wondering the same question since last week, but I still cannot figure out what happened.\r\n\r\nAccording to the discussion with my friends, we guessed it might be caused by a new feature [node pruning](https://gist.github.com/yorickdowne/3323759b4cbf2022e191ab058a4276b2).\r\n\r\nOn 1/25, the client version is 1.10.12, and then on 1/26, it changes to 1.10.15.\r\nSo we estimate that maintenance operators might upgrade the client version and do offline pruning at the same time.\r\n\r\nBecause I have not used pruning before, I do not know the root cause of dropping is (or might be) related to this new feature.\r\n\r\nMaybe you could follow the article above to test how big would disk usage be cut off.\r\nMany thanks.",
